220\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:46:36.817Z\",\"durationMs\":420000,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"iteration\":2,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:46:36.817Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Define Q3 bounded STUDY selection, transformation, authority, provenance, anti-injection, leakage, and adversarial-fixture protocol at pre-WRITE\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"All 5 findings newly operationalize the md-generator selection, transformation, authority, provenance/injection, leakage-check, and adversarial-fixture contract.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q3\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q3\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Two-style exemplar pairing or multi-style synthesis\",\"Rank-only exemplar selection\",\"Raw exemplar content in the writer prompt\",\"Attribution as permission for exact reuse\",\"Silent leak redaction\"],\"focusTrack\":\"study-protocol\",\"edgeCase\":\"ambiguous-input\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"Glob\",\"Grep\",\"Bash\",\"apply_patch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:66-191\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:89-118\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:257-274\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:376-380\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/build-write-prompt.ts:102-154\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/iterations/iteration-001.md:16-18\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/iterations/iteration-002.md:15-25\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:53:19.000Z\",\"durationMs\":390000,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":3,\"iterationCount\":3,\"minIterations\":3,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:53:19.000Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"iteration\":3,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:53:19.000Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -27,9 +27,9 @@\n ## 3. Key Questions\n \n - [x] Q1. Where exactly do formatters-v3, prompt/schema assets, and the EXTRACT -> WRITE -> VALIDATE -> REPORT pipeline create quality limits that corpus evidence can address?\n - [x] Q2. What do representative and corpus-wide DESIGN.md section shapes and token vocabularies imply for a calibrated, versioned output schema without forcing homogeneity?\n-- [ ] Q3. How should few-shot exemplars or study pairs be selected, transformed, and isolated so they improve reasoning while preserving target-measured truth and anti-copy discipline?\n+- [x] Q3. How should few-shot exemplars or study pairs be selected, transformed, and isolated so they improve reasoning while preserving target-measured truth and anti-copy discipline?\n - [ ] Q4. Which consistency metrics, quality baselines, validators, and fixtures can be derived from the corpus, and where should each run in the pipeline?\n - [ ] Q5. Which smart or out-of-the-box integrations offer the best quality lift per build cost, and what phased implementation sequence should follow?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n@@ -50,24 +50,27 @@\n ## 6. Answered Questions\n \n - Q1 answered in iteration 1: the safe corpus attachment points are a separate STUDY/pre-WRITE context builder, `buildWritePrompt` between locked facts and prose work, a shared versioned schema manifest, additive corpus-calibrated validation, and generated corpus fixtures. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:14-24]\n - Q2 answered in iteration 2: use a stable required spine, capability-conditional sections, ordered extension slots, a Quick Start capability matrix, category/value-shape distributions, semantic typography roles with validated extensions, and stratified absence/anomaly fixtures. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:15-25]\n+- Q3 answered in iteration 3: select up to three cards but hydrate one coherent bundle's DESIGN/tokens pair; transform it into de-literalized observations; bind it to target facts before WRITE; fail closed on generation/provenance/rights/injection; and run leakage checks before ordinary validation. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:15-25]\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 7. What Worked\n \n - Pipeline-first tracing exposed enforceable insertion points before corpus sampling and preserved the target-measured truth boundary. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:62-66]\n - Complete deterministic corpus scans separated structural invariants from conditional capabilities and retained theme/family variance. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:64-68]\n+- Resolving “study pair” against the live one-site-at-a-time router and predecessor mode table prevented accidental two-style synthesis. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:66-70]\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 8. What Failed\n \n - Spec Kit Memory initialization call failed with `Connection closed`; direct canonical reads replaced it.\n - The v3 reference, emitter, and validator do not share one machine-readable schema contract, creating observable drift that later calibration must surface rather than hide. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:20-22]\n - A first anomaly probe failed on Python quoting and succeeded after a bounded correction; no evidence gap remained. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:40-45]\n+- Broad keyword search returned sibling-mode noise; narrow evidence reads closed Q3 without using the tangents. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:66-70]\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 9. Exhausted Approaches\n@@ -80,8 +83,9 @@\n \n - Plain full-corpus prompt loading, BM25-only authority, raw token averaging, and multi-style palette blending were already eliminated by predecessor research. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:311-332]\n - Corpus evidence in EXTRACT or REPORT, exemplar rewrites of deterministic values, and the static prompt template as the sole runtime hook are ruled out by the live pipeline. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:26-30]\n - Corpus-majority homogenization, one exact H2 sequence, fixed token counts, and a closed enum containing every observed typography label are ruled out. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:27-38]\n+- Two-style pairs, rank-only selection, raw exemplar prompt injection, attribution-as-permission, and silent leak redaction are ruled out. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:27-38]\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n ## 11A. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n@@ -92,9 +96,9 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. Next Focus\n \n-Define Q3's bounded STUDY protocol at the pre-WRITE insertion point: select coherent study pairs using calibrated capabilities, specify what the model may learn versus copy, carry provenance/rights/anti-copy gates, and preserve locked target facts. Include negative and adversarial cases.\n+Answer Q4 by defining corpus-derived consistency metrics, quality baselines, and compact generated fixture packs at the shared schema/emitter/prompt/leak-check/validator boundaries. Calibrate enforceable versus advisory thresholds, false-positive controls, and deterministic CI/update behavior.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. Research Boundaries\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n@@ -3,13 +3,8 @@\n   \"generation\": 1,\n   \"status\": \"iterating\",\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n     {\n-      \"id\": \"Q3\",\n-      \"text\": \"How should exemplars or study pairs improve reasoning without overriding measured truth or anti-copy controls?\",\n-      \"status\": \"open\"\n-    },\n-    {\n       \"id\": \"Q4\",\n       \"text\": \"Which quality baselines, validators, and fixtures can be derived from the corpus?\",\n       \"status\": \"open\"\n     },\n@@ -32,8 +27,15 @@\n       \"text\": \"What corpus section shapes and token vocabularies imply for a calibrated output schema?\",\n       \"status\": \"resolved\",\n       \"iteration\": 2,\n       \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-002.md:15-25\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"text\": \"How should exemplars or study pairs improve reasoning without overriding measured truth or anti-copy controls?\",\n+      \"status\": \"resolved\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-003.md:15-25\"\n     }\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\n@@ -113,8 +115,48 @@\n       \"question\": \"Q2\",\n       \"summary\": \"Theme/capability variance and observed contract mismatches should drive stratified baselines and anomaly fixtures.\",\n       \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:25\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"I003-F1\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Select up to three eligible cards, then hydrate one same-bundle DESIGN.md plus design-tokens.json pair; never two styles.\",\n+      \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:17\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"I003-F2\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Transform the selected pair into source-pointer-backed de-literalized observations with explicit prohibited reuse.\",\n+      \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:19\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"I003-F3\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Bind STUDY to a target-facts digest and insert it after FACTS but before prose work, never in deterministic sections.\",\n+      \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:21\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"I003-F4\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Use a fail-closed generation, provenance, rights/use-label, and prompt-injection envelope; raw corpus text never reaches the writer.\",\n+      \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:23\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"I003-F5\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Run target-value and source-overlap leakage checks before normal validation with positive, negative, stale, rights, injection, mismatch, capability, copy, and false-positive fixtures.\",\n+      \"roughBuildCost\": \"3-5 engineer-days\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:25\"]\n     }\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     {\n@@ -132,13 +174,13 @@\n   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 10,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 2,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 15,\n     \"convergenceScore\": 0,\n     \"coverageBySources\": {}\n   },\n-  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-18T12:46:36.817Z\"\n+  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-18T12:53:19.000Z\"\n }\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -13,20 +13,21 @@\n | Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n | 1 | Live pipeline and schema/validator boundaries | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n | 2 | Corpus-calibrated schema and vocabulary | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n+| 3 | Bounded STUDY protocol for safe exemplars | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n \n ## Question Status\n \n-- Answered: 2/5 (40%)\n-- Resolved: Q1, Q2\n-- Remaining: Q3, Q4, Q5\n+- Answered: 3/5 (60%)\n+- Resolved: Q1, Q2, Q3\n+- Remaining: Q4, Q5\n \n ## Convergence Trend\n \n-- Ratios: `1.00 -> 1.00`\n-- Minimum iterations: 2/3\n-- Composite vote: rolling/MAD unavailable; question coverage is 0.40 and votes CONTINUE\n+- Ratios: `1.00 -> 1.00 -> 1.00`\n+- Minimum iterations: 3/3, passed\n+- Composite vote: rolling average CONTINUE; MAD unavailable; question coverage 0.60 CONTINUE\n - Legal stop: not eligible\n \n ## Key Findings\n \n@@ -36,20 +37,23 @@\n - Corpus-calibrated checks should extend, not replace, current fidelity validation.\n - Generated corpus summaries and selected edge bundles can supply regression fixtures.\n - The calibrated schema should use a stable spine, capability-conditional sections, ordered extension slots, and a shared Quick Start matrix.\n - Token and typography calibration should preserve stratified ranges, semantic core roles, valid extensions, and source labels.\n+- STUDY should hydrate one matched bundle pair and pass only de-literalized observations bound to a target-facts digest.\n+- Provenance/rights/injection gates and pre-validation leakage checks must fail closed with no-study fallback.\n \n ## Dead Ends\n \n - Corpus evidence in EXTRACT or REPORT.\n - Exemplar rewrites of deterministic target values.\n - Static prompt template as the only enforceable integration point.\n - Corpus-majority section homogenization or fixed median token counts.\n - Closed typography vocabulary copied from every observed label.\n+- Two-style exemplar pairing, raw exemplar prompt injection, and rank-only selection.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Bounded STUDY-pair selection, transformation, provenance, and anti-copy controls for Q3.\n+Corpus-derived metrics, quality baselines, threshold classes, and deterministic fixture/CI design for Q4.\n \n ## Active Risks\n \n - Schema-reference, emitter, and validator drift is unresolved.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/orchestration-status.log\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/orchestration-status.log\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/orchestration-status.log\n@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@\n {\"event\":\"started\",\"label\":\"sol\",\"at\":\"2026-07-18T12:34:32.826Z\",\"duration_ms\":0,\"loop_type\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\"},\"gauges\":{\"iterations\":0,\"elapsed_ms\":0,\"score\":0}}\n {\"event\":\"progress\",\"label\":\"sol\",\"at\":\"2026-07-18T12:38:10.234Z\",\"duration_ms\":217408,\"loop_type\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1,\"run\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",\"gauges\":{\"iterations\":1,\"elapsed_ms\":217408,\"score\":1.0}}\n {\"event\":\"progress\",\"label\":\"sol\",\"at\":\"2026-07-18T12:46:36.817Z\",\"duration_ms\":724000,\"loop_type\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1,\"run\":2,\"status\":\"complete\",\"gauges\":{\"iterations\":2,\"elapsed_ms\":724000,\"score\":1.0}}\n+{\"event\":\"progress\",\"label\":\"sol\",\"at\":\"2026-07-18T12:53:19.000Z\",\"duration_ms\":1127000,\"loop_type\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1,\"run\":3,\"status\":\"complete\",\"gauges\":{\"iterations\":3,\"elapsed_ms\":1127000,\"score\":1.0}}\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-state.jsonl","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-state.jsonl","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-state.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-state.jsonl\n@@ -4,4 +4,6 @@\n {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"iteration\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:38:10.234Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":2,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Deterministic corpus calibration of section shape, Quick Start coverage, token vocabulary, typography roles, and meaningful absences\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"All 5 findings are new corpus-wide measurements or newly evidenced schema comparisons for Q2.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q2\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q2\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Corpus-majority section homogenization\",\"One exact H2 sequence\",\"Fixed token counts from corpus medians\",\"Closed typography-role enum from every observed label\"],\"focusTrack\":\"schema-calibration\",\"edgeCase\":\"contradictory-evidence\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"Bash\",\"apply_patch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"command: deterministic Python corpus calibration over .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles\",\"command: narrow anomaly probe over corpus DESIGN.md and design-tokens.json\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/design_md_format.md:71-300\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/formatters-v3.ts:117-239\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/099-supply/DESIGN.md:1-333\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/099-supply/design-tokens.json:1-220\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:46:36.817Z\",\"durationMs\":420000,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"iteration\":2,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:46:36.817Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Define Q3 bounded STUDY selection, transformation, authority, provenance, anti-injection, leakage, and adversarial-fixture protocol at pre-WRITE\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"All 5 findings newly operationalize the md-generator selection, transformation, authority, provenance/injection, leakage-check, and adversarial-fixture contract.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q3\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q3\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Two-style exemplar pairing or multi-style synthesis\",\"Rank-only exemplar selection\",\"Raw exemplar content in the writer prompt\",\"Attribution as permission for exact reuse\",\"Silent leak redaction\"],\"focusTrack\":\"study-protocol\",\"edgeCase\":\"ambiguous-input\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"Glob\",\"Grep\",\"Bash\",\"apply_patch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:66-191\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:89-118\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:257-274\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:376-380\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/build-write-prompt.ts:102-154\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/iterations/iteration-001.md:16-18\",\".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/iterations/iteration-002.md:15-25\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:53:19.000Z\",\"durationMs\":390000,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":3,\"iterationCount\":3,\"minIterations\":3,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:53:19.000Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"iteration\":3,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-18T12:53:19.000Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1}\n","additions":2,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -27,9 +27,9 @@\n ## 3. Key Questions\n \n - [x] Q1. Where exactly do formatters-v3, prompt/schema assets, and the EXTRACT -> WRITE -> VALIDATE -> REPORT pipeline create quality limits that corpus evidence can address?\n - [x] Q2. What do representative and corpus-wide DESIGN.md section shapes and token vocabularies imply for a calibrated, versioned output schema without forcing homogeneity?\n-- [ ] Q3. How should few-shot exemplars or study pairs be selected, transformed, and isolated so they improve reasoning while preserving target-measured truth and anti-copy discipline?\n+- [x] Q3. How should few-shot exemplars or study pairs be selected, transformed, and isolated so they improve reasoning while preserving target-measured truth and anti-copy discipline?\n - [ ] Q4. Which consistency metrics, quality baselines, validators, and fixtures can be derived from the corpus, and where should each run in the pipeline?\n - [ ] Q5. Which smart or out-of-the-box integrations offer the best quality lift per build cost, and what phased implementation sequence should follow?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n@@ -50,24 +50,27 @@\n ## 6. Answered Questions\n \n - Q1 answered in iteration 1: the safe corpus attachment points are a separate STUDY/pre-WRITE context builder, `buildWritePrompt` between locked facts and prose work, a shared versioned schema manifest, additive corpus-calibrated validation, and generated corpus fixtures. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:14-24]\n - Q2 answered in iteration 2: use a stable required spine, capability-conditional sections, ordered extension slots, a Quick Start capability matrix, category/value-shape distributions, semantic typography roles with validated extensions, and stratified absence/anomaly fixtures. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:15-25]\n+- Q3 answered in iteration 3: select up to three cards but hydrate one coherent bundle's DESIGN/tokens pair; transform it into de-literalized observations; bind it to target facts before WRITE; fail closed on generation/provenance/rights/injection; and run leakage checks before ordinary validation. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:15-25]\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 7. What Worked\n \n - Pipeline-first tracing exposed enforceable insertion points before corpus sampling and preserved the target-measured truth boundary. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:62-66]\n - Complete deterministic corpus scans separated structural invariants from conditional capabilities and retained theme/family variance. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:64-68]\n+- Resolving “study pair” against the live one-site-at-a-time router and predecessor mode table prevented accidental two-style synthesis. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:66-70]\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 8. What Failed\n \n - Spec Kit Memory initialization call failed with `Connection closed`; direct canonical reads replaced it.\n - The v3 reference, emitter, and validator do not share one machine-readable schema contract, creating observable drift that later calibration must surface rather than hide. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:20-22]\n - A first anomaly probe failed on Python quoting and succeeded after a bounded correction; no evidence gap remained. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:40-45]\n+- Broad keyword search returned sibling-mode noise; narrow evidence reads closed Q3 without using the tangents. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:66-70]\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 9. Exhausted Approaches\n@@ -80,8 +83,9 @@\n \n - Plain full-corpus prompt loading, BM25-only authority, raw token averaging, and multi-style palette blending were already eliminated by predecessor research. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:311-332]\n - Corpus evidence in EXTRACT or REPORT, exemplar rewrites of deterministic values, and the static prompt template as the sole runtime hook are ruled out by the live pipeline. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:26-30]\n - Corpus-majority homogenization, one exact H2 sequence, fixed token counts, and a closed enum containing every observed typography label are ruled out. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:27-38]\n+- Two-style pairs, rank-only selection, raw exemplar prompt injection, attribution-as-permission, and silent leak redaction are ruled out. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:27-38]\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n ## 11A. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n@@ -92,9 +96,9 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. Next Focus\n \n-Define Q3's bounded STUDY protocol at the pre-WRITE insertion point: select coherent study pairs using calibrated capabilities, specify what the model may learn versus copy, carry provenance/rights/anti-copy gates, and preserve locked target facts. Include negative and adversarial cases.\n+Answer Q4 by defining corpus-derived consistency metrics, quality baselines, and compact generated fixture packs at the shared schema/emitter/prompt/leak-check/validator boundaries. Calibrate enforceable versus advisory thresholds, false-positive controls, and deterministic CI/update behavior.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. Research Boundaries\n","additions":6,"deletions":2},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n@@ -3,13 +3,8 @@\n   \"generation\": 1,\n   \"status\": \"iterating\",\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n     {\n-      \"id\": \"Q3\",\n-      \"text\": \"How should exemplars or study pairs improve reasoning without overriding measured truth or anti-copy controls?\",\n-      \"status\": \"open\"\n-    },\n-    {\n       \"id\": \"Q4\",\n       \"text\": \"Which quality baselines, validators, and fixtures can be derived from the corpus?\",\n       \"status\": \"open\"\n     },\n@@ -32,8 +27,15 @@\n       \"text\": \"What corpus section shapes and token vocabularies imply for a calibrated output schema?\",\n       \"status\": \"resolved\",\n       \"iteration\": 2,\n       \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-002.md:15-25\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"text\": \"How should exemplars or study pairs improve reasoning without overriding measured truth or anti-copy controls?\",\n+      \"status\": \"resolved\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-003.md:15-25\"\n     }\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\n@@ -113,8 +115,48 @@\n       \"question\": \"Q2\",\n       \"summary\": \"Theme/capability variance and observed contract mismatches should drive stratified baselines and anomaly fixtures.\",\n       \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:25\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"I003-F1\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Select up to three eligible cards, then hydrate one same-bundle DESIGN.md plus design-tokens.json pair; never two styles.\",\n+      \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:17\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"I003-F2\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Transform the selected pair into source-pointer-backed de-literalized observations with explicit prohibited reuse.\",\n+      \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:19\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"I003-F3\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Bind STUDY to a target-facts digest and insert it after FACTS but before prose work, never in deterministic sections.\",\n+      \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:21\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"I003-F4\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Use a fail-closed generation, provenance, rights/use-label, and prompt-injection envelope; raw corpus text never reaches the writer.\",\n+      \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:23\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"I003-F5\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Run target-value and source-overlap leakage checks before normal validation with positive, negative, stale, rights, injection, mismatch, capability, copy, and false-positive fixtures.\",\n+      \"roughBuildCost\": \"3-5 engineer-days\",\n+      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:25\"]\n     }\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     {\n@@ -132,13 +174,13 @@\n   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 10,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 2,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 15,\n     \"convergenceScore\": 0,\n     \"coverageBySources\": {}\n   },\n-  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-18T12:46:36.817Z\"\n+  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-18T12:53:19.000Z\"\n }\n","additions":52,"deletions":10},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -13,20 +13,21 @@\n | Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n | 1 | Live pipeline and schema/validator boundaries | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n | 2 | Corpus-calibrated schema and vocabulary | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n+| 3 | Bounded STUDY protocol for safe exemplars | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n \n ## Question Status\n \n-- Answered: 2/5 (40%)\n-- Resolved: Q1, Q2\n-- Remaining: Q3, Q4, Q5\n+- Answered: 3/5 (60%)\n+- Resolved: Q1, Q2, Q3\n+- Remaining: Q4, Q5\n \n ## Convergence Trend\n \n-- Ratios: `1.00 -> 1.00`\n-- Minimum iterations: 2/3\n-- Composite vote: rolling/MAD unavailable; question coverage is 0.40 and votes CONTINUE\n+- Ratios: `1.00 -> 1.00 -> 1.00`\n+- Minimum iterations: 3/3, passed\n+- Composite vote: rolling average CONTINUE; MAD unavailable; question coverage 0.60 CONTINUE\n - Legal stop: not eligible\n \n ## Key Findings\n \n@@ -36,20 +37,23 @@\n - Corpus-calibrated checks should extend, not replace, current fidelity validation.\n - Generated corpus summaries and selected edge bundles can supply regression fixtures.\n - The calibrated schema should use a stable spine, capability-conditional sections, ordered extension slots, and a shared Quick Start matrix.\n - Token and typography calibration should preserve stratified ranges, semantic core roles, valid extensions, and source labels.\n+- STUDY should hydrate one matched bundle pair and pass only de-literalized observations bound to a target-facts digest.\n+- Provenance/rights/injection gates and pre-validation leakage checks must fail closed with no-study fallback.\n \n ## Dead Ends\n \n - Corpus evidence in EXTRACT or REPORT.\n - Exemplar rewrites of deterministic target values.\n - Static prompt template as the only enforceable integration point.\n - Corpus-majority section homogenization or fixed median token counts.\n - Closed typography vocabulary copied from every observed label.\n+- Two-style exemplar pairing, raw exemplar prompt injection, and rank-only selection.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Bounded STUDY-pair selection, transformation, provenance, and anti-copy controls for Q3.\n+Corpus-derived metrics, quality baselines, threshold classes, and deterministic fixture/CI design for Q4.\n \n ## Active Risks\n \n - Schema-reference, emitter, and validator drift is unresolved.\n","additions":11,"deletions":7},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/orchestration-status.log","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/orchestration-status.log","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/orchestration-status.log\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/orchestration-status.log\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/orchestration-status.log\n@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@\n {\"event\":\"started\",\"label\":\"sol\",\"at\":\"2026-07-18T12:34:32.826Z\",\"duration_ms\":0,\"loop_type\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\"generation\":1,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\"},\"gauges\":{\"iterations\":0,\"elapsed_ms\":0,\"score\":0}}\n {\"event\":\"progress\",\"label\":\"sol\",\"at\":\"2026-07-18T12:38:10.234Z