{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784379932967,"sessionID":"ses_08acca7b4ffeXv97nbzMOKS10V","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2TIlqzGMvN1rTfUIF8F3jvx8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\n3:   \"generation\": 1,\n4:   \"status\": \"iterating\",\n5:   \"openQuestions\": [\n6:     {\n7:       \"id\": \"Q4\",\n8:       \"text\": \"Which quality baselines, validators, and fixtures can be derived from the corpus?\",\n9:       \"status\": \"open\"\n10:     },\n11:     {\n12:       \"id\": \"Q5\",\n13:       \"text\": \"Which smart integrations offer the best quality lift per build cost?\",\n14:       \"status\": \"open\"\n15:     }\n16:   ],\n17:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n18:     {\n19:       \"id\": \"Q1\",\n20:       \"text\": \"Where exactly do formatters-v3 and pipeline stages create quality limits that corpus evidence can address?\",\n21:       \"status\": \"resolved\",\n22:       \"iteration\": 1,\n23:       \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-001.md:14-24\"\n24:     },\n25:     {\n26:       \"id\": \"Q2\",\n27:       \"text\": \"What corpus section shapes and token vocabularies imply for a calibrated output schema?\",\n28:       \"status\": \"resolved\",\n29:       \"iteration\": 2,\n30:       \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-002.md:15-25\"\n31:     },\n32:     {\n33:       \"id\": \"Q3\",\n34:       \"text\": \"How should exemplars or study pairs improve reasoning without overriding measured truth or anti-copy controls?\",\n35:       \"status\": \"resolved\",\n36:       \"iteration\": 3,\n37:       \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-003.md:15-25\"\n38:     }\n39:   ],\n40:   \"keyFindings\": [\n41:     {\n42:       \"id\": \"I001-F1\",\n43:       \"iteration\": 1,\n44:       \"question\": \"Q1\",\n45:       \"summary\": \"The guided pipeline stops before DESIGN.md authorship; corpus reasoning belongs in a separate STUDY/pre-WRITE phase, not EXTRACT, VALIDATE, or REPORT.\",\n46:       \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/guided-run.ts:151-229\"]\n47:     },\n48:     {\n49:       \"id\": \"I001-F2\",\n50:       \"iteration\": 1,\n51:       \"question\": \"Q1\",\n52:       \"summary\": \"buildWritePrompt is the narrowest bounded few-shot insertion point after locked facts and before prose work.\",\n53:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n54:       \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/build-write-prompt.ts:102-154\"]\n55:     },\n56:     {\n57:       \"id\": \"I001-F3\",\n58:       \"iteration\": 1,\n59:       \"question\": \"Q1\",\n60:       \"summary\": \"A shared versioned section/field manifest is needed because the v3 reference, Quick Start emitter, and heading validator drift.\",\n61:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-4 engineer-days\",\n62:       \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/design_md_format.md:235-300\", \".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/formatters-v3.ts:187-238\", \".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/validate.ts:279-310\"]\n63:     },\n64:     {\n65:       \"id\": \"I001-F4\",\n66:       \"iteration\": 1,\n67:       \"question\": \"Q1\",\n68:       \"summary\": \"Corpus-calibrated structure and vocabulary checks should be additive after existing fidelity checks and before score calculation.\",\n69:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"3-5 engineer-days\",\n70:       \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/validate.ts:248-496\"]\n71:     },\n72:     {\n73:       \"id\": \"I001-F5\",\n74:       \"iteration\": 1,\n75:       \"question\": \"Q1\",\n76:       \"summary\": \"Generated corpus summaries plus selected edge bundles can extend current compact fixtures without loading all raw bundles in tests.\",\n77:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n78:       \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/tests/formatters-v3.test.ts:5-60\", \".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/tests/validate.test.ts:35-208\"]\n79:     },\n80:     {\n81:       \"id\": \"I002-F1\",\n82:       \"iteration\": 2,\n83:       \"question\": \"Q2\",\n84:       \"summary\": \"The corpus supports a stable required spine, conditional capability sections, and ordered extension slots rather than one exact sequence.\",\n85:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-4 engineer-days\",\n86:       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:17\"]\n87:     },\n88:     {\n89:       \"id\": \"I002-F2\",\n90:       \"iteration\": 2,\n91:       \"question\": \"Q2\",\n92:       \"summary\": \"Quick Start needs a shared capability matrix for source, requiredness, omission predicates, and CSS/Tailwind eligibility.\",\n93:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-4 engineer-days\",\n94:       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:19\"]\n95:     },\n96:     {\n97:       \"id\": \"I002-F3\",\n98:       \"iteration\": 2,\n99:       \"question\": \"Q2\",\n100:       \"summary\": \"Token calibration should version category/value shapes and stratified ranges without enforcing median counts or filling absences.\",\n101:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n102:       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:21\"]\n103:     },\n104:     {\n105:       \"id\": \"I002-F4\",\n106:       \"iteration\": 2,\n107:       \"question\": \"Q2\",\n108:       \"summary\": \"Typography needs a stable semantic core-role normalizer plus namespaced validated extensions and preserved source labels.\",\n109:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n110:       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:23\"]\n111:     },\n112:     {\n113:       \"id\": \"I002-F5\",\n114:       \"iteration\": 2,\n115:       \"question\": \"Q2\",\n116:       \"summary\": \"Theme/capability variance and observed contract mismatches should drive stratified baselines and anomaly fixtures.\",\n117:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n118:       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:25\"]\n119:     },\n120:     {\n121:       \"id\": \"I003-F1\",\n122:       \"iteration\": 3,\n123:       \"question\": \"Q3\",\n124:       \"summary\": \"Select up to three eligible cards, then hydrate one same-bundle DESIGN.md plus design-tokens.json pair; never two styles.\",\n125:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n126:       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:17\"]\n127:     },\n128:     {\n129:       \"id\": \"I003-F2\",\n130:       \"iteration\": 3,\n131:       \"question\": \"Q3\",\n132:       \"summary\": \"Transform the selected pair into source-pointer-backed de-literalized observations with explicit prohibited reuse.\",\n133:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n134:       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:19\"]\n135:     },\n136:     {\n137:       \"id\": \"I003-F3\",\n138:       \"iteration\": 3,\n139:       \"question\": \"Q3\",\n140:       \"summary\": \"Bind STUDY to a target-facts digest and insert it after FACTS but before prose work, never in deterministic sections.\",\n141:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n142:       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:21\"]\n143:     },\n144:     {\n145:       \"id\": \"I003-F4\",\n146:       \"iteration\": 3,\n147:       \"question\": \"Q3\",\n148:       \"summary\": \"Use a fail-closed generation, provenance, rights/use-label, and prompt-injection envelope; raw corpus text never reaches the writer.\",\n149:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n150:       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:23\"]\n151:     },\n152:     {\n153:       \"id\": \"I003-F5\",\n154:       \"iteration\": 3,\n155:       \"question\": \"Q3\",\n156:       \"summary\": \"Run target-value and source-overlap leakage checks before normal validation with positive, negative, stale, rights, injection, mismatch, capability, copy, and false-positive fixtures.\",\n157:       \"roughBuildCost\": \"3-5 engineer-days\",\n158:       \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:25\"]\n159:     }\n160:   ],\n161:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n162:     {\n163:       \"approach\": \"Plain full-corpus loading or raw token averaging\",\n164:       \"reason\": \"Eliminated by predecessor research because it destroys coherence and increases context/copy risk.\",\n165:       \"source\": \".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:311-332\"\n166:     }\n167:   ],\n168:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n169:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n170:   \"graphDecision\": null,\n171:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n172:   \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n173:   \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n174:   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n175:   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n176:   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n177:   \"metrics\": {\n178:     \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n179:     \"openQuestions\": 2,\n180:     \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n181:     \"keyFindings\": 15,\n182:     \"convergenceScore\": 0,\n183:     \"coverageBySources\": {}\n184:   },\n185:   \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-18T12:53:19.000Z\"\n186: }\n\n(End of file - total 186 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"status\": \"iterating\",\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"Q4\",\n      \"text\": \"Which quality baselines, validators, and fixtures can be derived from the corpus?\",\n      \"status\": \"open\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"Q5\",\n      \"text\": \"Which smart integrations offer the best quality lift per build cost?\",\n      \"status\": \"open\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"Q1\",\n      \"text\": \"Where exactly do formatters-v3 and pipeline stages create quality limits that corpus evidence can address?\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"status\": \"iterating\",\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"Q4\",\n      \"text\": \"Which quality baselines, validators, and fixtures can be derived from the corpus?\",\n      \"status\": \"open\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"Q5\",\n      \"text\": \"Which smart integrations offer the best quality lift per build cost?\",\n      \"status\": \"open\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"Q1\",\n      \"text\": \"Where exactly do formatters-v3 and pipeline stages create quality limits that corpus evidence can address?\",\n      \"status\": \"resolved\",\n      \"iteration\": 1,\n      \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-001.md:14-24\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"Q2\",\n      \"text\": \"What corpus section shapes and token vocabularies imply for a calibrated output schema?\",\n      \"status\": \"resolved\",\n      \"iteration\": 2,\n      \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-002.md:15-25\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"Q3\",\n      \"text\": \"How should exemplars or study pairs improve reasoning without overriding measured truth or anti-copy controls?\",\n      \"status\": \"resolved\",\n      \"iteration\": 3,\n      \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-003.md:15-25\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"keyFindings\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I001-F1\",\n      \"iteration\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Q1\",\n      \"summary\": \"The guided pipeline stops before DESIGN.md authorship; corpus reasoning belongs in a separate STUDY/pre-WRITE phase, not EXTRACT, VALIDATE, or REPORT.\",\n      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/guided-run.ts:151-229\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I001-F2\",\n      \"iteration\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Q1\",\n      \"summary\": \"buildWritePrompt is the narrowest bounded few-shot insertion point after locked facts and before prose work.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/build-write-prompt.ts:102-154\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I001-F3\",\n      \"iteration\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Q1\",\n      \"summary\": \"A shared versioned section/field manifest is needed because the v3 reference, Quick Start emitter, and heading validator drift.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-4 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/design_md_format.md:235-300\", \".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/formatters-v3.ts:187-238\", \".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/validate.ts:279-310\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I001-F4\",\n      \"iteration\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Q1\",\n      \"summary\": \"Corpus-calibrated structure and vocabulary checks should be additive after existing fidelity checks and before score calculation.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"3-5 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/validate.ts:248-496\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I001-F5\",\n      \"iteration\": 1,\n      \"question\": \"Q1\",\n      \"summary\": \"Generated corpus summaries plus selected edge bundles can extend current compact fixtures without loading all raw bundles in tests.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/tests/formatters-v3.test.ts:5-60\", \".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/tests/validate.test.ts:35-208\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I002-F1\",\n      \"iteration\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Q2\",\n      \"summary\": \"The corpus supports a stable required spine, conditional capability sections, and ordered extension slots rather than one exact sequence.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-4 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:17\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I002-F2\",\n      \"iteration\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Q2\",\n      \"summary\": \"Quick Start needs a shared capability matrix for source, requiredness, omission predicates, and CSS/Tailwind eligibility.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-4 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:19\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I002-F3\",\n      \"iteration\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Q2\",\n      \"summary\": \"Token calibration should version category/value shapes and stratified ranges without enforcing median counts or filling absences.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:21\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I002-F4\",\n      \"iteration\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Q2\",\n      \"summary\": \"Typography needs a stable semantic core-role normalizer plus namespaced validated extensions and preserved source labels.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:23\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I002-F5\",\n      \"iteration\": 2,\n      \"question\": \"Q2\",\n      \"summary\": \"Theme/capability variance and observed contract mismatches should drive stratified baselines and anomaly fixtures.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-002.md:25\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I003-F1\",\n      \"iteration\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n      \"summary\": \"Select up to three eligible cards, then hydrate one same-bundle DESIGN.md plus design-tokens.json pair; never two styles.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:17\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I003-F2\",\n      \"iteration\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n      \"summary\": \"Transform the selected pair into source-pointer-backed de-literalized observations with explicit prohibited reuse.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"2-3 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:19\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I003-F3\",\n      \"iteration\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n      \"summary\": \"Bind STUDY to a target-facts digest and insert it after FACTS but before prose work, never in deterministic sections.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:21\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I003-F4\",\n      \"iteration\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n      \"summary\": \"Use a fail-closed generation, provenance, rights/use-label, and prompt-injection envelope; raw corpus text never reaches the writer.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"1-2 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:23\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"I003-F5\",\n      \"iteration\": 3,\n      \"question\": \"Q3\",\n      \"summary\": \"Run target-value and source-overlap leakage checks before normal validation with positive, negative, stale, rights, injection, mismatch, capability, copy, and false-positive fixtures.\",\n      \"roughBuildCost\": \"3-5 engineer-days\",\n      \"sources\": [\"iterations/iteration-003.md:25\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"Plain full-corpus loading or raw token averaging\",\n      \"reason\": \"Eliminated by predecessor research because it destroys coherence and increases context/copy risk.\",\n      \"source\": \".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:311-332\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n  \"graphDecision\": null,\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n  \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n  \"observedIdeas\": [],\n  \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n  \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n  \"metrics\": {\n    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n    \"openQuestions\": 2,\n    \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n    \"keyFindings\": 15,\n    \"convergenceScore\": 0,\n    \"coverageBySources\": {}\n  },\n  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-18T12:53:19.000Z\"\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":186,"totalLines":186,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1784379932953,"end":1784379932967}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_057efe74801c1815016a5b7a1ccf008191b7efbd95d10c56d4"}},"id":"prt_f75550116001yc2oyO01ZTEFu2","sessionID":"ses_08acca7b4ffeXv97nbzMOKS10V","messageID":"msg_f7554af52001nS226Sn5PLWabX"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784379932983,"sessionID":"ses_08acca7b4ffeXv97nbzMOKS10V","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ds7ueJx4KuWZURyblxrkagfn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":55,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n55: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n56: \n57: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n58: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n59: ## 7. What Worked\n60: \n61: - Pipeline-first tracing exposed enforceable insertion points before corpus sampling and preserved the target-measured truth boundary. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:62-66]\n62: - Complete deterministic corpus scans separated structural invariants from conditional capabilities and retained theme/family variance. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:64-68]\n63: - Resolving “study pair” against the live one-site-at-a-time router and predecessor mode table prevented accidental two-style synthesis. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:66-70]\n64: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n65: \n66: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n67: ## 8. What Failed\n68: \n69: - Spec Kit Memory initialization call failed with `Connection closed`; direct canonical reads replaced it.\n70: - The v3 reference, emitter, and validator do not share one machine-readable schema contract, creating observable drift that later calibration must surface rather than hide. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:20-22]\n71: - A first anomaly probe failed on Python quoting and succeeded after a bounded correction; no evidence gap remained. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:40-45]\n72: - Broad keyword search returned sibling-mode noise; narrow evidence reads closed Q3 without using the tangents. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:66-70]\n73: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n74: \n75: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n76: ## 9. Exhausted Approaches\n77: \n78: None yet.\n79: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n80: \n81: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n82: ## 10. Ruled-Out Directions\n83: \n84: - Plain full-corpus prompt loading, BM25-only authority, raw token averaging, and multi-style palette blending were already eliminated by predecessor research. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:311-332]\n85: - Corpus evidence in EXTRACT or REPORT, exemplar rewrites of deterministic values, and the static prompt template as the sole runtime hook are ruled out by the live pipeline. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:26-30]\n86: - Corpus-majority homogenization, one exact H2 sequence, fixed token counts, and a closed enum containing every observed typography label are ruled out. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:27-38]\n87: - Two-style pairs, rank-only selection, raw exemplar prompt injection, attribution-as-permission, and silent leak redaction are ruled out. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:27-38]\n88: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n89: \n90: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n91: ## 11A. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n92: \n93: - Which exact scoring weights and schema thresholds remain robust across diverse style families?\n94: - Where should the retrieval executable be packaged during implementation?\n95: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n96: \n97: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n98: ## 11. Next Focus\n99: \n100: Answer Q4 by defining corpus-derived consistency metrics, quality baselines, and compact generated fixture packs at the shared schema/emitter/prompt/leak-check/validator boundaries. Calibrate enforceable versus advisory thresholds, false-positive controls, and deterministic CI/update behavior.\n101: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n102: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n103: \n104: ## 12. Research Boundaries\n105: \n106: - Maximum iterations: 10\n107: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n108: - Stop policy: convergence\n109: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n110: - Progressive synthesis: false; final `research.md` is workflow-owned\n111: - Allowed writes: this detached lineage only\n112: - Session: `fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt`\n\n(End of file - total 112 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. What Worked\n\n- Pipeline-first tracing exposed enforceable insertion points before corpus sampling and preserved the target-measured truth boundary. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:62-66]\n- Complete deterministic corpus scans separated structural invariants from conditional capabilities and retained theme/family variance. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:64-68]\n- Resolving “study pair” against the live one-site-at-a-time router and predecessor mode table prevented accidental two-style synthesis. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:66-70]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. What Failed\n\n- Spec Kit Memory initialization call failed with `Connection closed`; direct canonical reads replaced it.\n- The v3 reference, emitter, and validator do not share one machine-readable schema contract, creating observable drift that later calibration must surface rather than hide. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:20-22]\n- A first anomaly probe failed on Python quoting and succeeded after a bounded correction; no evidence gap remained. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:40-45]\n- Broad keyword search returned sibling-mode noise; narrow evidence reads closed Q3 without using the tangents. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:66-70]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. What Worked\n\n- Pipeline-first tracing exposed enforceable insertion points before corpus sampling and preserved the target-measured truth boundary. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:62-66]\n- Complete deterministic corpus scans separated structural invariants from conditional capabilities and retained theme/family variance. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:64-68]\n- Resolving “study pair” against the live one-site-at-a-time router and predecessor mode table prevented accidental two-style synthesis. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:66-70]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. What Failed\n\n- Spec Kit Memory initialization call failed with `Connection closed`; direct canonical reads replaced it.\n- The v3 reference, emitter, and validator do not share one machine-readable schema contract, creating observable drift that later calibration must surface rather than hide. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:20-22]\n- A first anomaly probe failed on Python quoting and succeeded after a bounded correction; no evidence gap remained. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:40-45]\n- Broad keyword search returned sibling-mode noise; narrow evidence reads closed Q3 without using the tangents. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:66-70]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. Exhausted Approaches\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. Ruled-Out Directions\n\n- Plain full-corpus prompt loading, BM25-only authority, raw token averaging, and multi-style palette blending were already eliminated by predecessor research. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md:311-332]\n- Corpus evidence in EXTRACT or REPORT, exemplar rewrites of deterministic values, and the static prompt template as the sole runtime hook are ruled out by the live pipeline. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:26-30]\n- Corpus-majority homogenization, one exact H2 sequence, fixed token counts, and a closed enum containing every observed typography label are ruled out. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:27-38]\n- Two-style pairs, rank-only selection, raw exemplar prompt injection, attribution-as-permission, and silent leak redaction are ruled out. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:27-38]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n\n- Which exact scoring weights and schema thresholds remain robust across diverse style families?\n- Where should the retrieval executable be packaged during implementation?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. Next Focus\n\nAnswer Q4 by defining corpus-derived consistency metrics, quality baselines, and compact generated fixture packs at the shared schema/emitter/prompt/leak-check/validator boundaries. Calibrate enforceable versus advisory thresholds, false-positive controls, and deterministic CI/update behavior.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. Research Boundaries\n\n- Maximum iterations: 10\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Stop policy: convergence\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: false; final `research.md` is workflow-owned\n- Allowed writes: this detached lineage only\n- Session: `fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt`","lineStart":55,"lineEnd":112,"totalLines":112,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784379932964,"end":1784379932981}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_057efe74801c1815016a5b7a1ccf6081918712692dbb136ae1"}},"id":"prt_f75550120001sB7Hp2lTjF2dDB","sessionID":"ses_08acca7b4ffeXv97nbzMOKS10V","messageID":"msg_f7554af52001nS226Sn5PLWabX"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784379932985,"sessionID":"ses_08acca7b4ffeXv97nbzMOKS10V","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3ecNSHL5TVG12es86PWg2aTs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Dashboard: SOL Lineage\n2: \n3: ## Lifecycle\n4: \n5: - Status: iterating\n6: - Session: `fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt`\n7: - Generation: 1\n8: - Executor: `cli-opencode` / `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`\n9: - Stop policy: convergence\n10: \n11: ## Iteration Table\n12: \n13: | Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n14: |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n15: | 1 | Live pipeline and schema/validator boundaries | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n16: | 2 | Corpus-calibrated schema and vocabulary | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n17: | 3 | Bounded STUDY protocol for safe exemplars | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n18: \n19: ## Question Status\n20: \n21: - Answered: 3/5 (60%)\n22: - Resolved: Q1, Q2, Q3\n23: - Remaining: Q4, Q5\n24: \n25: ## Convergence Trend\n26: \n27: - Ratios: `1.00 -> 1.00 -> 1.00`\n28: - Minimum iterations: 3/3, passed\n29: - Composite vote: rolling average CONTINUE; MAD unavailable; question coverage 0.60 CONTINUE\n30: - Legal stop: not eligible\n31: \n32: ## Key Findings\n33: \n34: - The workflow needs a separate STUDY/pre-WRITE boundary; corpus evidence must not alter EXTRACT, VALIDATE truth, or REPORT.\n35: - `buildWritePrompt` is the narrowest bounded exemplar insertion point.\n36: - A shared versioned schema manifest should unify reference, emitter, prompt, and validator expectations.\n37: - Corpus-calibrated checks should extend, not replace, current fidelity validation.\n38: - Generated corpus summaries and selected edge bundles can supply regression fixtures.\n39: - The calibrated schema should use a stable spine, capability-conditional sections, ordered extension slots, and a shared Quick Start matrix.\n40: - Token and typography calibration should preserve stratified ranges, semantic core roles, valid extensions, and source labels.\n41: - STUDY should hydrate one matched bundle pair and pass only de-literalized observations bound to a target-facts digest.\n42: - Provenance/rights/injection gates and pre-validation leakage checks must fail closed with no-study fallback.\n43: \n44: ## Dead Ends\n45: \n46: - Corpus evidence in EXTRACT or REPORT.\n47: - Exemplar rewrites of deterministic target values.\n48: - Static prompt template as the only enforceable integration point.\n49: - Corpus-majority section homogenization or fixed median token counts.\n50: - Closed typography vocabulary copied from every observed label.\n51: - Two-style exemplar pairing, raw exemplar prompt injection, and rank-only selection.\n52: \n53: ## Next Focus\n54: \n55: Corpus-derived metrics, quality baselines, threshold classes, and deterministic fixture/CI design for Q4.\n56: \n57: ## Active Risks\n58: \n59: - Schema-reference, emitter, and validator drift is unresolved.\n60: - Spec Kit Memory unavailable; direct canonical evidence is being used.\n61: - No convergence or quality-guard stop candidate yet.\n\n(End of file - total 61 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Dashboard: SOL Lineage\n\n## Lifecycle\n\n- Status: iterating\n- Session: `fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt`\n- Generation: 1\n- Executor: `cli-opencode` / `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`\n- Stop policy: convergence\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Live pipeline and schema/validator boundaries | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n| 2 | Corpus-calibrated schema and vocabulary | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n| 3 | Bounded STUDY protocol for safe exemplars | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md","text":"# Deep Research Dashboard: SOL Lineage\n\n## Lifecycle\n\n- Status: iterating\n- Session: `fanout-sol-1784377726143-umj0lt`\n- Generation: 1\n- Executor: `cli-opencode` / `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`\n- Stop policy: convergence\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Live pipeline and schema/validator boundaries | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n| 2 | Corpus-calibrated schema and vocabulary | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n| 3 | Bounded STUDY protocol for safe exemplars | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n- Answered: 3/5 (60%)\n- Resolved: Q1, Q2, Q3\n- Remaining: Q4, Q5\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n- Ratios: `1.00 -> 1.00 -> 1.00`\n- Minimum iterations: 3/3, passed\n- Composite vote: rolling average CONTINUE; MAD unavailable; question coverage 0.60 CONTINUE\n- Legal stop: not eligible\n\n## Key Findings\n\n- The workflow needs a separate STUDY/pre-WRITE boundary; corpus evidence must not alter EXTRACT, VALIDATE truth, or REPORT.\n- `buildWritePrompt` is the narrowest bounded exemplar insertion point.\n- A shared versioned schema manifest should unify reference, emitter, prompt, and validator expectations.\n- Corpus-calibrated checks should extend, not replace, current fidelity validation.\n- Generated corpus summaries and selected edge bundles can supply regression fixtures.\n- The calibrated schema should use a stable spine, capability-conditional sections, ordered extension slots, and a shared Quick Start matrix.\n- Token and typography calibration should preserve stratified ranges, semantic core roles, valid extensions, and source labels.\n- STUDY should hydrate one matched bundle pair and pass only de-literalized observations bound to a target-facts digest.\n- Provenance/rights/injection gates and pre-validation leakage checks must fail closed with no-study fallback.\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- Corpus evidence in EXTRACT or REPORT.\n- Exemplar rewrites of deterministic target values.\n- Static prompt template as the only enforceable integration point.\n- Corpus-majority section homogenization or fixed median token counts.\n- Closed typography vocabulary copied from every observed label.\n- Two-style exemplar pairing, raw exemplar prompt injection, and rank-only selection.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nCorpus-derived metrics, quality baselines, threshold classes, and deterministic fixture/CI design for Q4.\n\n## Active Risks\n\n- Schema-reference, emitter, and validator drift is unresolved.\n- Spec Kit Memory unavailable; direct canonical evidence is being used.\n- No convergence or quality-guard stop candidate yet.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":61,"totalLines":61,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1784379932969,"end":1784379932984}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_057efe74801c1815016a5b7a1ccf6c819191cb7e1aa6145b70"}},"id":"prt_f75550125001myhqJOWKfcjt5R","sessionID":"ses_08acca7b4ffeXv97nbzMOKS10V","messageID":"msg_f7554af52001nS226Sn5PLWabX"}}
