 quality control per build cost and dependency fit.\"}\n5: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"I005-F4\",\"iteration\":5,\"question\":\"Q5\",\"summary\":\"Raw/multi-style prompting, automatic fixture updates, uncalibrated fuzzy enforcement, vector replatforming, fine-tuning, and LLM-judge gates are rejected until deterministic controls leave a measured residual gap.\",\"sources\":[\"iterations/iteration-002.md:27-38\",\"iterations/iteration-003.md:27-38\",\"iterations/iteration-004.md:27-39\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-33\"]}\n6: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"I005-F5\",\"iteration\":5,\"question\":\"Q5\",\"summary\":\"Q1-Q5 coverage is complete, but run 5's 0.80 new-information ratio exceeds the 0.05 numeric convergence threshold; remaining calibration unknowns are non-blocking and need a narrow verification pass rather than broad research.\",\"sources\":[\"deep-research-config.json:3-18\",\"deep-research-strategy.md:29-45\",\"deep-research-strategy.md:94-104\"],\"inference\":\"Answered-question completeness and numeric convergence are distinct gates.\"}\n\n(End of file - total 6 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":5,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":5,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Rank all md-generator upgrade levers and define the phased implementation sequence for Q5\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.8,\"noveltyJustification\":\"2 of 5 findings were fully new and 3 partially synthesized prior evidence; a +0.10 simplicity bonus for resolving Q5 raised the ratio from 0.70 to 0.80.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q5\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q5\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Raw or multi-style exemplar prompting\",\"Fuzzy similarity as enforcement before labeled calibration\",\"Automatic CI fixture regeneration\",\"Vector replatforming, fine-tuni